If you want the Excel formula version for `J2`, use:

```excel
=IF(H2="","No",IF(H2="N/A","N/A",IF(OR(H2="Yes",ISNUMBER(H2)),"Yes","No")))
```

Then fill down through `J4`.

This works because:
- blank `H` → `"No"`
- `H` = `"N/A"` → `"N/A"`
- `H` = `"Yes"` or a date value → `"Yes"`

Note: Excel stores dates as numbers, so `ISNUMBER(H2)` catches date cells.
